^^^ a gap... Decided to test 15+ minutes with mac address rotation

time 13:46 - (around device 09:00) turned iOS ble off/on again (new mac address). Will now wait 15 mins
 - It appears BLEDB logs two devices macs and doesn't remove old one immediately if new device with same payload is seen
  - Not necessarily a bad thing in case a bad actor is impersonating another device... let's see if it affects memory usage (old mac should be removed after 15 mins)

device 10:46 unplugged htc vive base stations

NOTE: Doesn't appear to be advertising any longer - can it do this whilst scanning? If not we have to alter the logic in connection manager.

19:04.826 - Appears to print devices and kicj back in to life, but still no advertisements seen on iOS.

After 1000 seconds (15 mins = 900 seconds) only appears to remove VALID devices (old iOS mac with read payload), not HTC Vive hardware... may be a timing thing... lets wait to see.

24:03 ish - appears to never remove open connection for a long time... double check logic to ensure this is happening by design and not by coincidence
